Yes.

7
00:00:15,780 --> 00:00:17,480
The ideal gas of point particles.

8
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:18,680
Now,

9
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,940
I want to talk about the ideal

10
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:23,200
gas of particles which are not point particles.

11
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,960
Under what circumstances is a gas

12
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:28,720
well approximated by an ideal gas?

13
00:00:29,420 --> 00:00:31,420
An ideal gas is one where

14
00:00:31,420 --> 00:00:33,420
particles don't collide with each other.

15
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:35,450
And the answer is when the

16
00:00:35,450 --> 00:00:37,340
density of the gas is low enough.

17
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,200
And it doesn't matter very much if the

18
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,820
particles themselves have some size and some structure,

19
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:46,780
as long as the distance between particles is much,

20
00:00:46,780 --> 00:00:49,560
much larger than the structure of

21
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:50,280
the particle itself,

22
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:52,300
it's still an ideal gas.

23
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,480
So particles in this,

24
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:54,760
particles,

25
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:55,440
molecules,

26
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:56,000
and so forth,

27
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,460
molecules certainly have structure.

28
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,980
They can rotate,

29
00:00:58,980 --> 00:01:00,100
they can vibrate.

30
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,800
But this leads to a very

31
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:07,000
big paradox in classical statistical mechanics.

32
00:01:07,580 --> 00:01:09,650
And it is one that

33
00:01:09,650 --> 00:01:11,720
was only resolved by quantum mechanics.

34
00:01:12,260 --> 00:01:16,200
It was considered one of the big paradoxes about classical,

35
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:19,000
about statistical mechanics

36
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:21,520
at the end of the 19th century.

37
00:01:21,820 --> 00:01:22,800
And as I said,

38
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:23,180
it only...

39
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,970
It only got resolved by the

40
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:28,740
same ideas that resolved the problem,

41
00:01:28,740 --> 00:01:30,440
essentially almost exactly

42
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,320
the same ideas,

43
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:35,060
which resolved the big problem about black body radiation,

44
00:01:35,060 --> 00:01:37,020
which we will

45
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:37,540
come to.

46
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,410
So if you don't know what

47
00:01:39,410 --> 00:01:40,920
the problem of black body radiation is,

48
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:41,760
don't worry about it right

49
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,020
now.

50
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:44,800
The problem of molecules had a very,

51
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:47,320
very similar flavor to it.

52
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:48,920
And let me tell you

53
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,140
what the problem of molecules is.

54
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,740
And we'll do it by doing an example.

55
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:53,180
Okay.

56
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,160
So let's say we have a molecule with structure.

57
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:56,280
Now,

58
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:58,120
this is a very,

59
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:03,260
very simplified version of the structure of a molecule.

60
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,979
But it's enough to see what the problem is.

61
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:16,040
Let's replace the point molecule.

62
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:16,960
Oh,

63
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,440
darn it.

64
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:31,120
Let's replace the point molecule by a pair of atoms,

65
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:35,400
which are connected by a rigid

66
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:35,800
rod.

67
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:36,920
Now,

68
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:39,400
in the notes that are on the internet,

69
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,720
which are available to you,

70
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,380
I did the problem

71
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:49,460
explicitly of a molecule built like this,

72
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:52,740
which is free to rotate around in three dimensions.

73
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,180
Okay.

74
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:55,320
So I'm going to simplify it here,

75
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,560
because all of the essence of

76
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,800
it is in a simpler story.

77
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:00,840
Namely,

78
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:05,460
the molecule is only free to rotate in a plane.

79
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:06,960
All right.

80
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:12,660
So the molecule is free to rotate around an axis.

81
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:16,080
And the axis could be one of the atoms.

82
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:19,279
A simple example would be that there's

83
00:03:19,279 --> 00:03:21,780
a heavy atom and a light atom.

84
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,230
The heavier atom will tend

85
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:27,260
not to move around so much,

86
00:03:27,260 --> 00:03:29,540
and the light atom will revolve around

87
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:33,540
it at the end of this entirely rigid rod.

88
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:34,700
Okay.

89
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:40,460
The atom has,

90
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:45,980
in addition to the usual kinetic energy of motion,

91
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,620
overall motion,

92
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:48,980
it has an

93
00:03:48,980 --> 00:03:50,540
additional energy of rotation.

94
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:54,940
And that additional energy of rotation can be excited,

95
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,300
for example,

96
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,300
by collisions between

97
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,380
two such molecules.

98
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,220
Two such molecules come together,

99
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:02,160
and they hit each other off center,

100
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,400
and even if they

101
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,360
weren't rotating,

102
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:04,680
they would rotate.

103
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,760
And after they hit each other,

104
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,740
they will start rotating.

105
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:10,280
So the rotational energy is part of the energy,

106
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,800
and it has to be accounted for in studying

107
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,650
the statistical mechanics and the energetics

108
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:16,500
of this gas of these molecules.

109
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:18,660
Okay.

110
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:25,700
So let's first consider the energy of rotation.

111
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:27,340
And as I said,

112
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:27,980
for simplicity,

113
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:29,400
this is purely for simplicity,

114
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,900
let's take one of the atoms

115
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:34,360
to be heavy enough that it moves.

116
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:34,660
Okay.

117
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,400
And it's a much lower velocity than the other one.

118
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:37,220
Really,

119
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:37,780
of course,

120
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:42,940
the complex system rotates about its center of mass.

121
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,080
But if one of the atoms is heavy,

122
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,920
then the center of mass is close to that atom.

123
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:49,060
It's like the solar system.

124
00:04:49,420 --> 00:04:51,580
The solar system revolves around the sun.

125
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:52,180
Well,

126
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:52,640
not quite.

127
00:04:52,940 --> 00:04:54,840
The earth doesn't quite revolve around the sun.

128
00:04:54,940 --> 00:04:56,790
The sun and the earth revolve around the point

129
00:04:56,790 --> 00:04:58,640
which is the center of mass of the sun and

130
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:58,940
the earth,

131
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:01,080
assuming we didn't have to worry about Jupiter.

132
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:04,660
But it's not such a big deal.

133
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:06,050
It's just such a bad approximation to put the

134
00:05:06,050 --> 00:05:07,440
sun at the center and say the earth moves

135
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:07,980
around it.

136
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:10,140
And in that case,

137
00:05:10,140 --> 00:05:14,280
you can ignore the motion of the central one,

138
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:14,900
the heavy one,

139
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:15,820
and the

140
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,670
kinetic energy involved is just the kinetic

141
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,520
energy of the light one moving around.

142
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:20,540
Okay.

143
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,520
This is not essential.

144
00:05:21,740 --> 00:05:24,240
This is in no way essential to the story.

145
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:25,680
Okay.

146
00:05:25,780 --> 00:05:28,680
So what is the energy of such a molecule?

147
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,500
Well,

148
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,220
first of all,

149
00:05:30,220 --> 00:05:33,020
there's a translational degree of freedom of the molecule.

150
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:35,520
That just means the motion of the center of mass.

151
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:40,940
And its energy is exactly what you would expect.

152
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:44,370
It's the total momentum squared divided by

153
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:47,500
twice the total mass of the molecule.

154
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:51,750
I'll use capital M to indicate

155
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:54,580
the total mass of the composite molecule.

156
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,180
And that's one of the terms in the energy.

157
00:05:58,380 --> 00:05:58,800
And there's,

158
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,060
of course,

159
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,740
a term like that for each molecule,

160
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:01,940
so there's really a summation

161
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:02,340
sign,

162
00:06:02,340 --> 00:06:03,900
which I won't bother writing out.

163
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:07,300
And then there's the rotational energy.

164
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,380
So for the rotational energy,

165
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:11,860
let's just imagine the center of

166
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:14,340
mass is at one of these molecules,

167
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:16,860
and the other one gets to move in a circle.

168
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,060
It gets to move in a circle,

169
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,810
and let's take the radius of

170
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:23,560
the molecule to be small r.

171
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,040
Okay.

172
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,780
So what is the kinetic energy?

173
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:31,920
Let's take the light atom and make its mass r.

174
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,640
It's little m.

175
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:34,600
And of course,

176
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,560
the kinetic energy of rotation is

177
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:38,520
nothing but the kinetic energy of moving

178
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,500
around in the circle.

179
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:44,560
It's just m times the angular velocity,

180
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,640
not the angular velocity,

181
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,140
but the tangential velocity,

182
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:49,220
let's call it v squared,

183
00:06:49,220 --> 00:06:51,720
divided by 2.

184
00:06:52,020 --> 00:06:54,040
This is not the overall velocity.

185
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:57,460
This is the component of the velocity if we

186
00:06:57,460 --> 00:07:00,640
pretended that the center of mass was standing still.

187
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,120
It's the velocity around in the circular velocity,

188
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,460
and that's it.

189
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:06,360
That's the kinetic energy.

190
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,060
Let me rewrite that.

191
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:14,250
The velocity moving around in the

192
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:18,940
circle is proportional to the angular velocity.

193
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:22,120
So let's call the angular velocity theta dot,

194
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,340
the time derivative of the angle,

195
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:28,100
the angular

196
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,480
orientation of the molecule.

197
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,460
Theta dot times what?

198
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:32,320
r.

199
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:33,680
R.

200
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,520
Theta dot times r.

201
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:36,460
And we can plug this in here,

202
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:40,020
and this gives us m r squared.

203
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:43,500
And r now is not a dynamical variable.

204
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:47,010
It's the fixed length of the

205
00:07:47,010 --> 00:07:50,160
rigid rod connecting the two atoms.

206
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,410
That's of course associated with

207
00:07:52,410 --> 00:07:54,280
the rigidity of certain molecular bonds.

208
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:57,240
Sometimes molecular bonds are pretty rigid,

209
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,320
and this would be an instance in which the

210
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,200
molecular bond was very,

211
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:01,440
very rigid.

212
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:04,720
And it didn't allow much inward outward motion.

213
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:05,840
Now,

214
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:08,500
so this becomes m r squared over 2,

215
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:12,820
times theta dot squared.

216
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:16,600
Now,

217
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,980
m r squared,

218
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:22,260
is just a constant,

219
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:23,920
and has a name.

220
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,080
This is the moment of inertia.

221
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:27,550
So we can give it a

222
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:28,960
name and it's usually called i.

223
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,040
And again,

224
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,380
there's no Cin

225
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:31,380
n,

226
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:31,420
the moment of inertia.

227
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:33,539
times theta dot squared.

228
00:08:33,539 --> 00:08:35,799
And for our purposes,

229
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:38,820
the definition of the moment of inertia is nothing but

230
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,520
mr squared.

231
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,659
It's just a symbol that

232
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:43,799
I use to simplify the formula.

233
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:47,000
I over 2 times theta dot squared.

234
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,060
Now theta dot,

235
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:50,860
or theta,

236
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:51,800
excuse me,

237
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,020
is a generalized coordinate.

238
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:56,860
If we go back to our studies of mechanics,

239
00:08:56,860 --> 00:09:02,340
we remember that we can think of any possible description of the

240
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:07,820
coordinates of a system as being more or less on an equal footing,

241
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:13,160
and work either with position along here,

242
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,900
or we can work with angle,

243
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:18,920
and apply the standard rules of classical mechanics.

244
00:09:19,220 --> 00:09:22,100
The standard rules of classical mechanics involve,

245
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,220
among other things,

246
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:25,660
constructing a Hamiltonian,

247
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:26,840
which is a very simple thing.

248
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,340
Constructing momenta,

249
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:32,320
which are conjugate to the coordinates.

250
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,540
The coordinate in this case is theta,

251
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:39,260
and the momentum conjugate to it is called angular momentum.

252
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,560
Alright,

253
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,680
what is the rule?

254
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:42,820
Incidentally,

255
00:09:42,820 --> 00:09:45,220
this is the kinetic energy.

256
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:47,140
It's also the Lagrangian.

257
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:48,980
For those who like Lagrangians,

258
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:52,580
this happens to be the Lagrangian of the circular motion.

259
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,380
So think of it that way.

260
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:56,840
What is the definition of angular momentum?

261
00:09:56,840 --> 00:10:00,280
The definition of the momentum conjugate to theta.

262
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,440
Anybody remember the definition of conjugate momentum?

263
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,710
The derivative of the Lagrangian with respect

264
00:10:08,710 --> 00:10:11,720
to the time derivative of the coordinate.

265
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:13,380
So,

266
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:16,000
that just means the derivative of

267
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,620
the Lagrangian with respect to theta dot.

268
00:10:20,540 --> 00:10:22,480
So the angular momentum...

269
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,440
Now,

270
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,130
I had a reason for not

271
00:10:25,130 --> 00:10:26,820
writing that this is equal to theta.

272
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:27,140
It's equal to L,

273
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,000
the Lagrangian.

274
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:34,500
Because the standard symbol for angular momentum is also L.

275
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,960
Sorry about that.

276
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:41,120
The L that I'm writing here is not the Lagrangian.

277
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:42,580
It is the angular momentum,

278
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,460
standard symbol.

279
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,330
And it's equal to the derivative of

280
00:10:47,330 --> 00:10:49,680
this object with respect to theta dot.

281
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,920
Just as...

282
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:51,980
Well,

283
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:52,760
you know the story.

284
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,620
I don't have to tell you.

285
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:56,500
So the angular momentum is just I.

286
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,260
Theta dot.

287
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:01,660
Now,

288
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:02,160
again,

289
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,480
this is not Lagrangian.

