That's what we started with.

2028
01:19:40,140 --> 01:19:43,980
Here is the expression for the change in energy

2029
01:19:43,980 --> 01:19:46,580
when we throw in one bit of information.

2030
01:19:48,080 --> 01:19:52,240
So this then is the dE on the left-hand side

2031
01:19:52,480 --> 01:19:54,140
and on the right-hand side,

2032
01:19:55,019 --> 01:19:57,940
dS is equal to one unit of entropy,

2033
01:19:58,320 --> 01:19:59,840
and so this must be

2034
01:19:59,840 --> 01:20:01,360
the temperature of the black hole.

2035
01:20:02,600 --> 01:20:07,180
h bar C divided by its radius.

2036
01:20:07,780 --> 01:20:09,580
We can also write this,

2037
01:20:09,620 --> 01:20:11,340
and there's a numerical constant,

2038
01:20:11,660 --> 01:20:12,960
there's a numerical constant,

2039
01:20:13,260 --> 01:20:15,980
but we can also write this as h bar C

2040
01:20:15,980 --> 01:20:20,440
divided by the Schwarzschild radius,

2041
01:20:20,700 --> 01:20:22,020
which is 2mg.

2042
01:20:24,440 --> 01:20:25,140
All right,

2043
01:20:25,140 --> 01:20:27,260
the honest answer happens to be,

