01:27:47,040 --> 01:27:47,760
It's not the sun,

2244
01:27:47,760 --> 01:27:48,320
the black hole.

2245
01:27:49,200 --> 01:27:51,420
Would it be correct to say that

2246
01:27:52,999 --> 01:27:55,780
the maximum amount of energy per volume

2247
01:27:55,780 --> 01:27:57,680
is what's inside the black hole?

2248
01:27:58,360 --> 01:27:59,300
Maximum amount...

2249
01:27:59,300 --> 01:27:59,860
I'll say it again.

2250
01:27:59,960 --> 01:28:02,380
The entropy per unit volume

2251
01:28:03,419 --> 01:28:04,920
in the biggest area

2252
01:28:04,920 --> 01:28:08,000
would be basically what's inside the black hole.

2253
01:28:08,100 --> 01:28:08,520
That's the thing.

2254
01:28:10,180 --> 01:28:11,800
The more...the most...

2255
01:28:11,800 --> 01:28:13,940
I think this is what this is telling you.

2256
01:28:13,940 --> 01:28:15,360
The fact that the entropy

2257
01:28:16,540 --> 01:28:18,720
is proportional to the area

2258
01:28:18,720 --> 01:28:21,980
is that at least when viewed from outside,

2259
01:28:22,280 --> 01:28:24,320
the black hole doesn't have an interior.

2260
01:28:24,680 --> 01:28:27,340
All it has is a surface.

2261
01:28:28,260 --> 01:28:30,260
And this is closely connected with the fact

2262
01:28:30,940 --> 01:28:32,520
that somebody on the outside

2263
01:28:32,520 --> 01:28:34,360
dropping things into a black hole

2264
01:28:34,940 --> 01:28:37,620
